President Obama has announced his intent to nominate three individuals for key positions in the State Department. Esther Brimmer has been nominated for the role of Assistant Secretary for International Organizations. Phil Gordon has been nominated for the role of Assistant Secretary for European and Eurasian Affairs. Melanne Verveer has been nominated for the role of Ambassador-at-Large for Global Women's Issues. These individuals bring deep knowledge and expertise in their respective fields and are committed to strengthening American diplomacy. They will be joining a leadership team at the State Department that will work towards renewing America's security and standing in an uncertain world. Secretary Clinton has expressed her confidence in these nominees and emphasized the importance of smart power and the expertise and vision these individuals will bring to the State Department.